    <fr:title text="\top  preserves the property"><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\top ]]></fr:tex> preserves the property</fr:title>
  </fr:frontmatter>
  <fr:mainmatter>
    <html:p>As is usual, the situation with our nullary connectives is maybe a little weirder-feeling, but in fact much simpler.
Let's look at the case of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\top ]]></fr:tex>.
In both strong Kleene and Dunn-Belnap valuations, this sentence always receives the value <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathsf {\mathbf {T}}]]></fr:tex>; so it has the property.
That's it!</html:p>
  </fr:mainmatter>
